The paper deals with image recovery from undersampled linear measurements, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). The use of generative residual networks (ResNet) and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of statistical priors and the need for efficient architectures, which are topics in information theory (IT) and multimedia (MM).
